#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:248
#, no-c-format
msgid "Prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:251
#, no-c-format
msgid "Multipathing is managed at the device level."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:256
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The storage array you use for the multipathed device must support "
"multipathing. For more information, see <xref linkend=\"sec.multipath."
"hardware\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:263
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You need to configure multipathing only if multiple physical paths exist "
"between host bus adapters in the server and host bus controllers for the "
"block storage device. You configure multipathing for the logical device as "
"seen by the server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:271
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For some storage arrays, the vendor provides its own multipathing software "
"to manage multipathing for the array’s physical and logical devices. In this "
"case, you should follow the vendor’s instructions for configuring "
"multipathing for those devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:279
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When using multipathing in a virtualization environment, the multipathing is "
"controlled in the host server environment. Configure multipathing for the "
"device before you assign it to a virtual guest machine."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:289
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disk Management Tasks"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:290
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Perform the following disk management tasks before you attempt to configure "
"multipathing for a physical or logical device that has multiple paths:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:296
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use third-party tools to carve physical disks into smaller logical disks."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:301
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use third-party tools to partition physical or logical disks. If you change "
"the partitioning in the running system, the Device Mapper Multipath (DM-MP) "
"module does not automatically detect and reflect these changes. DM-MPIO must "
"be re-initialized, which usually requires a reboot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:309
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use third-party SAN array management tools to create and configure hardware "
"RAID devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:315
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use third-party SAN array management tools to create logical devices such as "
"LUNs. Logical device types that are supported for a given array depend on "
"the array vendor."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:325
#, no-c-format
msgid "Software RAIDs"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:326
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Linux software RAID management software runs on top of multipathing. For "
"each device that has multiple I/O paths and that you plan to use in a "
"software RAID, you must configure the device for multipathing before you "
"attempt to create the software RAID device. Automatic discovery of "
"multipathed devices is not available. The software RAID is not aware of the "
"multipathing management running underneath."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:334
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For information about setting up multipathing for existing software RAIDs, "
"see <xref linkend=\"sec.multipath.raid\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:341
#, no-c-format
msgid "High-Availability Solutions"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:342
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"High-availability solutions for clustering storage resources run on top of "
"the multipathing service on each node. Make sure that the configuration "
"settings in the <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file on each node "
"are consistent across the cluster."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:348
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure that multipath devices have the same name across all devices. "
"Refer to <xref linkend=\"sec.multipath.names.ha\"/> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:352
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Distributed Replicated Block Device (DRBD) high-availability solution "
"for mirroring devices across a LAN runs on top of multipathing. For each "
"device that has multiple I/O paths and that you plan to use in a DRDB "
"solution, you must configure the device for multipathing before you "
"configure DRBD."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:362
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Always Keep the <filename>initrd</filename> in Synchronization with the "
"System Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:366
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"One of the most important requirements when using Multipath is to make sure "
"that the <filename>initrd</filename> and the installed system behave the "
"same regarding the root file system and all other file systems required to "
"boot the system. If Multipath is enabled in the system, it also needs to be "
"enabled in the <filename>initrd</filename> and vice versa. See <xref linkend="
"\"sec.multipath.configuration.start\"/> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:374
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the <filename>initrd</filename> and the system are not synchronized, the "
"system will not properly boot and the start-up procedure will result in an "
"emergency shell. See <xref linkend=\"sec.multipath.trouble.root\"/> for "
"instructions on how to avoid or repair such a scenario."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:384
#, no-c-format
msgid "Multipath Management Tools"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:386
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The multipathing support in &productname; is based on the Device Mapper "
"Multipath module of the Linux kernel and the <systemitem>multipath-tools</"
"systemitem> user space package. You can use the Multiple Devices "
"Administration utility ( <command>multipath</command> ) to view the status "
"of multipathed devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:395
#, no-c-format
msgid "Device Mapper Multipath Module"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:396
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Device Mapper Multipath (DM-MP) module provides the multipathing "
"capability for Linux. DM-MPIO is the preferred solution for multipathing on "
"&productname;. It is the only multipathing option shipped with the product "
"that is completely supported by &suse;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:402
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"DM-MPIO features automatic configuration of the multipathing subsystem for a "
"large variety of setups. Configurations of up to eight paths to each device "
"are supported. Configurations are supported for active/passive (one path "
"active, others passive) or active/active (all paths active with round-robin "
"load balancing)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:409
#, no-c-format
msgid "The DM-MPIO framework is extensible in two ways:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:414
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using specific hardware handlers. For information, see <xref linkend=\"sec."
"multipath.hardware.handlers\" xrefstyle=\"HeadingOnPage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:420
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using load-balancing algorithms that are more sophisticated than the round-"
"robin algorithm."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:426
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The user space component of DM-MPIO takes care of automatic path discovery "
"and grouping, and automated path retesting, so that a previously failed path "
"is automatically reinstated when it becomes healthy again. This minimizes "
"the need for administrator attention in a production environment."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:432
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"DM-MPIO protects against failures in the paths to the device, and not "
"failures in the device itself. If one of the active paths is lost (for "
"example, a network adapter breaks or a fiber-optic cable is removed), I/O is "
"redirected to the remaining paths. If the configuration is active/passive, "
"then the path fails over to one of the passive paths. If you are using the "
"round-robin load-balancing configuration, the traffic is balanced across the "
"remaining healthy paths. If all active paths fail, inactive secondary paths "
"must be woken up, so failover occurs with a delay of approximately 30 "
"seconds."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:443
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a disk array has more than one storage processor, ensure that the SAN "
"switch has a connection to the storage processor that owns the LUNs you want "
"to access. On most disk arrays, all LUNs belong to both storage processors, "
"so both connections are active."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:450
#, no-c-format
msgid "Storage Processors"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:451
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On some disk arrays, the storage array manages the traffic through storage "
"processors so that it presents only one storage processor at a time. One "
"processor is active and the other one is passive until there is a failure. "
"If you are connected to the wrong storage processor (the one with the "
"passive path) you might not see the expected LUNs, or you might see the LUNs "
"but get errors when you try to access them."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:461
#, no-c-format
msgid "Multipath I/O Features of Storage Arrays"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:468
#, no-c-format
msgid "Features of Storage Arrays"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:482
#, no-c-format
msgid "Active/passive controllers"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:487
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"One controller is active and serves all LUNs. The second controller acts as "
"a standby. The second controller also presents the LUNs to the multipath "
"component so that the operating system knows about redundant paths. If the "
"primary controller fails, the second controller takes over, and it serves "
"all LUNs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:494
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In some arrays, the LUNs can be assigned to different controllers. A given "
"LUN is assigned to one controller to be its active controller. One "
"controller does the disk I/O for any LUN at a time, and the second "
"controller is the standby for that LUN. The second controller also presents "
"the paths, but disk I/O is not possible. Servers that use that LUN are "
"connected to the LUN’s assigned controller. If the primary controller for a "
"set of LUNs fails, the second controller takes over, and it serves all LUNs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:508
#, no-c-format
msgid "Active/active controllers"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:513
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Both controllers share the load for all LUNs, and can process disk I/O for "
"any LUN. If one controller fails, the second controller automatically "
"handles all traffic."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:522
#, no-c-format
msgid "Load balancing"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:527
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Device Mapper Multipath driver automatically load balances traffic "
"across all active paths."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:535
#, no-c-format
msgid "Controller failover"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:540
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When the active controller fails over to the passive, or standby, "
"controller, the Device Mapper Multipath driver automatically activates the "
"paths between the host and the standby, making them the primary paths."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:550
#, no-c-format
msgid "Boot/Root device support"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:555
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Multipathing is supported for the root ( <filename>/</filename> ) device in "
"&productname; 10 and later. The host server must be connected to the "
"currently active controller and storage processor for the boot device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:561
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Multipathing is supported for the <filename>/boot</filename> device in "
"&productname; 11 and later."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:570
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Device Mapper Multipath detects every path for a multipathed device as a "
"separate SCSI device. The SCSI device names take the form <filename>/dev/"
"sd<replaceable>N</replaceable></filename> , where <filename><replaceable>N</"
"replaceable></filename> is an autogenerated letter for the device, beginning "
"with a and issued sequentially as the devices are created, such as "
"<filename>/dev/sda</filename> , <filename>/dev/sdb</filename> , and so on. "
"If the number of devices exceeds 26, the letters are duplicated so that the "
"next device after <filename>/dev/sdz</filename> will be named <filename>/dev/"
"sdaa</filename> , <filename>/dev/sdab</filename> , and so on."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:582
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If multiple paths are not automatically detected, you can configure them "
"manually in the <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file. The "
"<filename>multipath.conf</filename> file does not exist until you create and "
"configure it. For information, see <xref linkend=\"sec.multipath.conf_file\" "
"xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:592
#, no-c-format
msgid "Multipath I/O Management Tools"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:593
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The packages <systemitem class=\"resource\">multipath-tools</systemitem> and "
"<systemitem class=\"resource\">kpartx</systemitem> provide tools that take "
"care of automatic path discovery and grouping. They automatically test the "
"path periodically, so that a previously failed path is automatically "
"reinstated when it becomes healthy again. This minimizes the need for "
"administrator attention in a production environment."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:602
#, no-c-format
msgid "Tools in the multipath-tools Package"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:609
#, no-c-format
msgid "Tool"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:623
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>multipath</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:628
#, no-c-format
msgid "Scans the system for multipathed devices and assembles them."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:635
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>multipathd</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:640
#, no-c-format
msgid "Waits for maps events, then executes <command>multipath</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:647
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>kpartx</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:652
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Maps linear devmaps to partitions on the multipathed device, which makes it "
"possible to create multipath monitoring for partitions on the device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:661
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>mpathpersist</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:666
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Manages SCSI-persistent reservations on Device Mapper Multipath devices.ppc"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:678
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using MDADM for Multipathed Devices"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:679
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Udev is the default device handler, and devices are automatically known to "
"the system by the Worldwide ID instead of by the device node name. This "
"resolves problems in previous releases of MDADM and LVM where the "
"configuration files ( <filename>mdadm.conf</filename> and <filename>lvm."
"conf)</filename> did not properly recognize multipathed devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:687
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As with LVM2, MDADM requires that the devices be accessed by the ID rather "
"than by the device node path. Therefore, the <systemitem>DEVICE</systemitem> "
"entry in <filename>/etc/mdadm.conf</filename> should be set as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:693
#, no-c-format
msgid "DEVICE /dev/disk/by-id/*"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:694
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are using user-friendly names, specify the path as follows so that "
"only the device mapper names are scanned after multipathing is configured:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:698
#, no-c-format
msgid "DEVICE /dev/disk/by-id/dm-uuid-.*-mpath-.*"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:702
#, no-c-format
msgid "The multipath Command"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:703
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the Linux <command>multipath(8)</command> command to configure and "
"manage multipathed devices. The general syntax for the command looks like "
"the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:708
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"multipath [-v verbosity_level] [-b bindings_file] [-d] [-h|-l|-ll|-f|-F|-B|-"
"c|-q|-r|-w|-W|-t] [-p failover|multibus|group_by_serial|group_by_prio|"
"group_by_node_name] [<replaceable>DEVICENAME</replaceable>]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:709
#, no-c-format
msgid "Refer to <command>man 8 multipath</command> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: bridgehead
#: storage_multipath.xml:712
#, no-c-format
msgid "General Examples"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:715
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:717
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configures all multipath devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:723
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath <replaceable>DEVICENAME</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:726
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configures a specific multipath device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:729
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Replace <replaceable>DEVICENAME</replaceable> with the device node name such "
"as <filename>/dev/sdb</filename> (as shown by udev in the $DEVNAME "
"variable), or in the <literal>major:minor</literal> format. The device may "
"alternatively be a multipath map name."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:738
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -f"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:740
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Selectively suppresses a multipath map, and its device-mapped partitions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:747
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -d"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:749
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Dry run. Displays potential multipath devices, but does not create any "
"devices and does not update device maps."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:756
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -v2 -d"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:758
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Displays multipath map information for potential multipath devices in a dry "
"run. The -v2 option shows only local disks. This verbosity level prints the "
"created or updated multipath names only for use to feed other tools like "
"kpartx."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:772
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -v2 <replaceable>DEVICENAME</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:775
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configures a specific potential multipath device and displays multipath map "
"information for it. This verbosity level prints only the created or updated "
"multipath names for use to feed other tools like <command>kpartx</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:781
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There is no output if the device already exists and there are no changes. "
"Use <command>multipath -ll</command> to see the status of configured "
"multipath devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:796
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -v3"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:798
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configures potential multipath devices and displays multipath map "
"information for them. This verbosity level prints all detected paths, "
"multipaths, and device maps. Both WWID and <literal>devnode</literal> "
"blacklisted devices are displayed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:807
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -v3 <replaceable>DEVICENAME</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:810
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configures a specific potential multipath device and displays information "
"for it. The -v3 option shows the full path list. This verbosity level prints "
"all detected paths, multipaths, and device maps. Both WWID and "
"<literal>devnode</literal> blacklisted devices are displayed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:827
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -ll"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:829
#, no-c-format
msgid "Displays the status of all multipath devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:835
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -ll <replaceable>DEVICENAME</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:838
#, no-c-format
msgid "Displays the status of a specified multipath device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:851
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -F"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:853
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Flushes all unused multipath device maps. This unresolves the multiple "
"paths; it does not delete the devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:860
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -F <replaceable>DEVICENAME</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:863
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Flushes unused multipath device maps for a specified multipath device. This "
"unresolves the multiple paths; it does not delete the device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:867
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Replace <replaceable>DEVICENAME</replaceable> with the device node name such "
"as <filename>/dev/sdb</filename> (as shown by <command>udev</command> in the "
"$DEVNAME variable), or in the <literal>major:minor</literal> format. The "
"device may alternatively be a multipath map name."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:877
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"multipath -p [ failover | multibus | group_by_serial | group_by_prio | "
"group_by_node_name ]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:879
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sets the group policy by specifying one of the group policy options that are "
"described in the following table:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:910
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"(Default) One path per priority group. You can use only one path at a time."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:935
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"One priority group per detected SCSI serial number (the controller node "
"worldwide number)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:948
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"One priority group per path priority value. Paths with the same priority are "
"in the same priority group. Priorities are determined by callout programs "
"specified as a global, per-controller, or per-multipath option in the "
"<filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> configuration file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:977
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:979
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Shows internal hardware table and active configuration of multipath. Refer "
"to <command>man multipath</command> for details about the configuration "
"parameters."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:990
#, no-c-format
msgid "The mpathpersist Utility"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:991
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>mpathpersist</command> utility can be used to manage SCSI "
"persistent reservations on Device Mapper Multipath devices. The general "
"syntax for the command looks like the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:996
#, no-c-format
msgid "mpathpersist [options] [device]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:997
#, no-c-format
msgid "Refer to <command>man 8 mpathpersist</command> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1000
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use this utility with the service action reservation key "
"( <literal>reservation_key</literal> attribute) in the <filename>/etc/"
"multipath.conf</filename> file to set persistent reservations for SCSI "
"devices. The attribute is not used by default. If it is not set, the "
"<command>multipathd</command> daemon does not check for persistent "
"reservation for newly discovered paths or reinstated paths."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1008
#, no-c-format
msgid "reservation_key &lt;<replaceable>RESERVATION_KEY</replaceable>&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1009
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can add the attribute to the <literal>defaults</literal> section or the "
"<literal>multipaths</literal> section. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1013
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"multipaths {\n"
"  multipath {\n"
"    wwid   XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX\n"
"    alias      yellow\n"
"    reservation_key  0x123abc\n"
"  }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1020
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set the <literal>reservation_key</literal> parameter for all mpath devices "
"applicable for persistent management, then restart the <systemitem class="
"\"daemon\">multipathd</systemitem> daemon by running the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1026
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;systemctl restart multipathd"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1027
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After it is set up, you can specify the reservation key in the "
"<command>mpathpersist</command> commands."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: bridgehead
#: storage_multipath.xml:1031
#, no-c-format
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1034
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"mpathpersist --out --register --param-sark=123abc --prout-type=5 -d /dev/"
"mapper/mpath9"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1036
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Register the Service Action Reservation Key for the <filename>/dev/mapper/"
"mpath9</filename> device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1043
#, no-c-format
msgid "mpathpersist -i -k -d /dev/mapper/mpath9"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1045
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Read the Service Action Reservation Key for the <filename>/dev/mapper/"
"mpath9</filename> device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1052
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"mpathpersist --out --reserve --param-sark=123abc --prout-type=8 -d /dev/"
"mapper/mpath9"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1054
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Reserve the Service Action Reservation Key for the <filename>/dev/mapper/"
