#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:4406
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring Default Settings for &zseries; Devices"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:4407
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Testing of the &zseries; device with multipathing has shown that the "
"<literal>dev_loss_tmo</literal> parameter should be set to infinity "
"(2147483647), and the <literal>fast_io_fail_tmo</literal> parameter should "
"be set to 5 seconds. If you are using &zseries; devices, modify the "
"<filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file to specify the values as "
"follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:4415
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"defaults {\n"
"       dev_loss_tmo 2147483647\n"
"       fast_io_fail_tmo 5\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:4419
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <literal>dev_loss_tmo</literal> parameter sets the number of seconds to "
"wait before marking a multipath link as bad. When the path fails, any "
"current I/O on that failed path fails. The default value varies according to "
"the device driver being used. To use the driver’s internal timeouts, set the "
"value to zero (0). It can also be set to \"infinity\" or 2147483647 which "
"sets it to the max value of 2147483647 seconds (68 years)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:4427
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <literal>fast_io_fail_tmo</literal> parameter sets the length of time to "
"wait before failing I/O when a link problem is detected. I/O that reaches "
"the driver fails. If I/O is in a blocked queue, the I/O does not fail until "
"the <literal>dev_loss_tmo</literal> time elapses and the queue is unblocked."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:4434
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you modify the <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file, the changes "
"are not applied until you update the multipath maps, or until the "
"<systemitem class=\"daemon\">multipathd</systemitem> daemon is restarted "
"( <command>systemctl restart multipathd</command> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:4443
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using Multipath with NetApp Devices"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:4444
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When using multipath for NetApp devices, we recommend the following settings "
"in the <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:4450
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set the default values for the following parameters globally for NetApp "
"devices:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:4454
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"max_fds max\n"
"queue_without_daemon no"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:4458
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set the default values for the following parameters for NetApp devices in "
"the hardware table:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:4462
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"dev_loss_tmo infinity\n"
"fast_io_fail_tmo 5\n"
"features \"3 queue_if_no_path pg_init_retries 50\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:4470
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using --noflush with Multipath Devices"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:4471
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <option>--noflush</option> option should always be used when running on "
"multipath devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:4475
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example, in scripts where you perform a table reload, you use the "
"<literal>--noflush</literal> option on resume to ensure that any outstanding "
"I/O is not flushed, because you need the multipath topology information."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:4481
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"load\n"
"resume --noflush"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:4486
#, no-c-format
msgid "SAN Timeout Settings When the Root Device Is Multipathed"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:4489
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A system with root ( <filename>/</filename> ) on a multipath device might "
"stall when all paths have failed and are removed from the system because a "
"<literal>dev_loss_tmo</literal> timeout is received from the storage "
"subsystem (such as Fibre Channel storage arrays)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:4495
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the system device is configured with multiple paths and the multipath "
"<literal>no_path_retry</literal> setting is active, you should modify the "
"storage subsystem’s <literal>dev_loss_tmo</literal> setting accordingly to "
"ensure that no devices are removed during an all-paths-down scenario. We "
"strongly recommend that you set the <literal>dev_loss_tmo</literal> value to "
"be equal to or higher than the <literal>no_path_retry</literal> setting from "
"multipath."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:4504
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The recommended setting for the storage subsystem’s <literal>dev_los_tmo</"
"literal> is"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:4508
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;dev_loss_tmo&gt; = &lt;no_path_retry&gt; * &lt;polling_interval&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:4509
#, no-c-format
msgid "where the following definitions apply for the multipath values:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:4514
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>no_path_retry</literal> is the number of retries for multipath I/O "
"until the path is considered to be lost, and queuing of IO is stopped."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:4521
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>polling_interval</literal> is the time in seconds between path "
"checks."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:4527
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each of these multipath values should be set from the <filename>/etc/"
"multipath.conf</filename> configuration file. For information, see <xref "
"linkend=\"sec.multipath.conf_file\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

